CC  This enzyme, formyl-CoA transferase, transfers coenzyme A from formyl-CoA to oxalate. It forms a pathway, together with oxalyl-CoA decarboxylase, for oxalate degradation; decarboxylation by the latter gene regenerates formyl-CoA. The two enzymes typically are encoded by a two-gene operon.
